-- ============================================================
-- scripts/seed/utah_statutes.sql
-- ============================================================
-- One-off seed for utah_statutes (table created in migration 0036).
-- 1387 sections extracted from le.utah.gov XML chapter downloads on
-- 2026-05-24 — Title 76 (Criminal Code) + Title 41 (Motor Vehicles).
--
-- Apply once to fresh D1:
--   npx wrangler d1 execute rmpg-flex --remote --file=scripts/seed/utah_statutes.sql
--
-- NOT a migration — re-running this on an already-seeded DB will dupe
-- rows (no UNIQUE constraint on citation; that's a separate hygiene
-- task). Skip if `SELECT COUNT(*) FROM utah_statutes` already > 0.
--
-- Source data parsed by .firecrawl/parse.py (kept in the worktree
-- that generated this — see incident-2026-05-24-dual-worker.md).
-- Each row's offense_level is the MOST SEVERE classification mentioned
-- in the section text; about 47% of rows have a classification (the
-- rest are definitional/procedural sections).
--
-- Provenance: https://le.utah.gov/xcode/Title76/ and Title41/, version
-- bundles dated 1800010118000101 (default) or 2025/2026 amendments for
-- chapters updated in those sessions.
-- ============================================================

-- Wraps in BEGIN/COMMIT so D1 applies atomically.
